    <h1>Rainbow Krispy Treats</h1>
    <p>This recipe is very simple to make that an amateur chef such as myself can make it with their eye's closed.</p>
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>1 box of fruity pebbles cereal (9-12 oz)</li>
      <li>1 bag of marshmallows (10 oz)</li>
      <li>6 tbsp unsalted butter</li>
      <li>1/2 tsp salt</li>
      <li>1/2 tsp vanilla extract</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Instructions</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Turn your stove onto medium-low</li>
        <li>Melt your butter</li>
        <li>Add in your bag of marshmallows and turn the heat off once it is all melted</li>
        <li>Add in vanilla extract and salt to adjust the taste</li>
        <li>Add all of your cereal and mix it into the mixture</li>
        <li>Pour your mixture into a 9x12 pan</li>
        <li>Wait 30 minutes until the krispy sets and you are ready to serve</li>
